nline-formula"{\textgreater}$^{\textrm{−1}}${\textless}/span{\textgreater}, the percent bias decreased from 20 \% to 13 \%, and the Nash–Sutcliffe efficiency increased from {\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}−{\textless}/span{\textgreater}0.46 to 0.4. Furthermore, the blue and green ET results from the dynamic SWAT{\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}+{\textless}/span{\textgreater} model were compared to the four remote sensing methods. The results show that the SWAT{\textless}span class="inline-formula"{\textgreater}+{\textless}/span{\textgreater} blue and green ET are similar to the van Eekelen method and performed better than the other three remote sensing methods. It is concluded that representation of seasonal land use dynamics produces better ET results, which provide better estimations of blue and green agricultural water consumption.{\textless}/p{\textgreater}},
	language = {English},
	number = {16},
	urldate = {2022-09-01},
